.well
  %p
    The Longitudinal System Analysis (LSA) is:
    %ul
      %li A report to the US Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) as
      %li A zip file containing 10 Comma-Separated Values (CSV) files
      %li Generated by a Homeless Management Information System (HMIS)
      %li For Continuums of Care for the Homeless (CoCs)
      %li Submitted annually via HUD's Homelessness Data Exchange (HDX 2.0)
      %li Used to produce HUD's Annual Homelessness Assessment Report (AHAR) to Congress and
      %li Provides the data for Stella, HUD's strategy and analysis tool for CoCs, available on HDX 2.0.
    = link_to 'https://www.hudexchange.info/resource/5726/lsa-report-specifications-and-tools/', target: :_blank do
      Official LSA report specifications and tools can be found on the HUD Exchange
  %p.border-top.pt-4
    = link_to history_hud_reports_lsas_path do
      See the history of all report runs and download zip files
  %p
    = link_to hud_reports_historic_lsas_path do
      Pre-FY 2022 LSAs
  %p
    = link_to new_hud_reports_lsa_path, class: 'btn btn-primary' do
      Generate New LSA
